you start looking up.

13
00:00:43.300 --> 00:00:46.249
I think the different perspective for
me came in terms of the org chart,

14
00:00:46.249 --> 00:00:49.447
where as a software engineer, I didn't
care about the organization chart,

15
00:00:49.447 --> 00:00:53.470
like where the team sit, who they report
to, which vertical or domain they're in.

16
00:00:53.470 --> 00:00:57.080
Now, it's really important cuz I need to
know which manager I need to talk to.

17
00:00:57.080 --> 00:01:01.770
You'll hear names and teams, and
you're like, what do they do?

18
00:01:01.770 --> 00:01:05.075
I need to know that pretty quickly,
so I had the org chart bookmarked so

19
00:01:05.075 --> 00:01:06.820
I know who people are talking about.

20
00:01:08.630 --> 00:01:13.284
My favorite perspective is staff meetings
where managers talk to other managers or

21
00:01:13.284 --> 00:01:17.483
directors and things like that, and
you're like, what goes on in those?

22
00:01:17.483 --> 00:01:19.347
It's really not that interesting,

23
00:01:19.347 --> 00:01:23.140
[LAUGH] there's no great secrets
you uncover in staff meetings.

24
00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:26.570
