00:03:06.008 --> 00:03:08.566
much everyone makes which was odd.

51
00:03:08.566 --> 00:03:11.478
&gt;&gt; Interesting.

52
00:03:11.478 --> 00:03:16.835
&gt;&gt; I would add to being in meetings
where you're creating policies,

53
00:03:16.835 --> 00:03:20.384
it's boring but it's fascinating [LAUGH].

54
00:03:20.384 --> 00:03:22.079
&gt;&gt; To add on to that, you're in it,

55
00:03:22.079 --> 00:03:25.785
you're added to a lot of meetings cuz
you're now the leader of the team.

56
00:03:25.785 --> 00:03:27.961
And you have no idea what's going on,

57
00:03:27.961 --> 00:03:33.280
cuz you have no idea what they're
talking about, you're just like, yeah.

58
00:03:33.280 --> 00:03:36.473
People might ask stuff of you and you're
like, let me get back to you on that,

59
00:03:36.473 --> 00:03:38.700
there's a lot of stuff you don't know.

60
00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:43.691
Because as a manager things just takes
longer to enact, there's projects in place

61
00:03:43.691 --> 00:03:48.325
that were already happening that you
weren't aware of, and now you are, and

62
00:03:48.325 --> 00:03:51.800
it's probably towards the end or
in the middle.

63
00:03:51.800 --> 00:03:55.230
There could be big announcements coming,
like a reorganization or

64
00:03:55.230 --> 00:03:58.780
maybe they're discussing someone,
maybe is on a performance plan,

65
00:03:58.780 --> 00:04:01.140
that usually doesn't
happen at staff level.

